      <h2 id='bRules'>Business Rules</h2><br>
      <ol>
        <li>Young customers must show ID at the store entrance or when purchasing the gift card.</li>
        <li>The creation of a transaction log must record the location, transaction status, payment amount and
          associate this
          information with the deposit code printed on the back of the card.</li>
        <li>Account authorization and creation must be done by the customer for security reasons.</li>
        <li>An unauthorized card cannot be loaded at the store immediately after purchase as there would be no
          account to
          deposit the money into.</li>
        <li>The customer must provide a valid password and PIN in order to authorize the gift card account.</li>
        <li>The customer must setup the gift card as a payee to their bank account and transfer funds to the card
          via payments
          or e-transfers.</li>
        <li>If the card is lost or stolen, the customer may deactivate it by logging onto the systemâ€™s website/app
          and using the
          PIN associated with the account.</li>
        <li>A deactivated card may be reactivated using the same method for deactivation once retrieved.</li>
      </ol>
